---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { brandName, contactEmail, engageHref, marketing } from '../site.config';
---

<Layout
  title={`Engage · ${brandName}`}
  description="Book a scoped discovery call with Sol Labs. Fit becomes a fixed statement of work."
  current="engage"
>
  <div class="page-wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>Scoped discovery, then a fixed SOW.</h1>
      <p>
        We do not sell open-ended hours on the first call. You get a short conversation to confirm
        ICP fit (usually Series B / growth on GCP with a GKE or model-fleet pain), then a written
        scope with a done definition.
      </p>

      <h2>What “done” looks like</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>A named outcome (for example: audit-shaped GKE + GitOps controls mapped to evidence)</li>
        <li>A time box (typical readiness sprint: weeks, not quarters)</li>
        <li>Artifacts your team keeps: Terraform/GitOps, control map, runbook</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who should book</h2>
      <p>{marketing.clarityLine}</p>

      <h2>Book</h2>
      <p>
        Prefer email while calendar booking is wired:
        <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}?subject=Sol%20Labs%20discovery`}>{contactEmail}</a>
      </p>
      <p class="meta">
        Replace this page’s CTA with your Cal.com (or equivalent) URL in
        <code>site.config.ts</code> → <code>engageHref</code> (currently {engageHref}).
      </p>
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href={`mailto:${contactEmail}?subject=Sol%20Labs%20discovery`}
        >Email to book</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
